content.detailedDescription:
At approximately 9 p.M. on saturday, september 7, 2013 i opened my basement door to toss a bag into the trash can that sits just outside.  this door opens to the east.  normally i would open the door, lean out, toss and then close the door.  tonight, as i leaned out, i clearly heard a voice in my head say, "you need to look up right now."  a large, bright orange light was stationary in the sky to the south and slightly east.  at this time, the light was the apparent size of a golf ball, however i did not have my glasses on.  i am very slightly nearsighted (uncorrected vision approx. 40-60/20). as i watched, the orange light slowly drifted down, slightly to the left, then rose again.  it did this a couple times over about a minute.  i felt glued in that spot, and i didn't want to take my eyes off it.  i kept waiting for it to vanish, but it just sort of lazily drifted up and down, side to side.  there was no wind or breeze where i was, and it was unusually silent outside.

i knew right away that this was not a conventional aircraft.  i live near seatac airport, and have never seen a light of this type in the sky.  neither was this light traveling in the usual pattern of air traffic.  as soon as i saw it, i knew it was not of this earth.  i felt and heard the presence of intelligence, and had the sense that this light was aware of me and wanted to be seen. 

i wanted to get a better look, and sensed i would be able to get my glasses and camera.  so i closed the basement door, ran upstairs and grabbed my glasses and phone, then went out my front door, which faces directly south.  it took less than 30 seconds to get from one door to the other.  the light was still in the sky, still in the south and slightly east (only 10? - 15? degrees east).  with my glasses on, the light was still large and bright orange, but now was somewhere between aspirin and dime sized.  it grew and shrank in size, and moved in a lazy way to the direct south.  it floated up and down as it traveled south.  then it stopped and split into three distinct, smaller orange lights.  these three lights floated up and down in unison, then merged back together into one larger light.  this one light shrank and dimmed then faded.  my sense was that it was turning and traveling away from me.  

the entire time i watched, i noted how very silent it was outside, and i live near two intersecting arterial streets.  it is difficult to describe how this sighting made me feel.  i was never scared, instead i felt calm, happy.  it seemed that the light projected this, and made me feel safe.  it seemed to project the information that it was here to "help."  i had my phone/camera in my hand, but again heard in my head not to bother, it wouldn't show up.  immediately after the light faded, i texted my husband to mark the date and time.

to my perception, the duration of the sighting was less than five minutes.  the time mark on the text i sent my husband is 9:04 p.M.
content.summary: A large, bright orange light visible for less than 5 minutes to the se.  slow, erratic path to s, split into 3 lights then merged back into one. slowly faded from sight.

content.detailedDescription:
This object may just be a satellite, however i have never seen a pulsating satellite.  the object travelled south to north with apparent speed and distance of a satellite, but pulsed.  

i noticed it first as a sudden bright light that slowly faded turned orange then red and faded black.  then further along its path it repeated the sequence, a sudden bright white light fading and turing orange then red finally black.  

from my view i observed this sequence 3 times, because of my limited field of view, my house to the south, and tree line to the north.  my field of view is about directly over head (my house obscuring view to south) and about 10 degrees to the north before trees obscure.

i can see the big dipper perfectly and the object passed through the handle, and next to the lowest star on the bottom of basin near the handle of the big dipper.

this object gave the appearence of possibly a satellite tumbling and changing reflection as it tumbled and reflected the sun from below the horizon, but i have never seen a satellite act that way with repeated pulsating and color change of light.
content.summary: From south to north like a pulsating satellite

content.detailedDescription:
Was over at my close friends house, relaxing outside, when our night turned to our inevitable scanning the skies for unusual objects. for awhile nothing but planes, but the skies were extremely clear. before i went home we talked in the front of the house for a few minutes. 

while we were outside, i first noticed a very small (starsize) blue object blinking and moving across the sky to the left, after only a few seconds it just vanished. less than 5 seconds later something burst in the same spot, with a fire like explosion, as if something was entering our atmosphere. after this bright orange yellow and glowing object burst into the sky out of nowhere, it began to move left across the sky leaving a large trail of smoke with a convex curve. the object hovered slowly and then began to make an s like trail with very abrupt accelerations and turns over the trees and out of our sight. 

i have seen many ufos down the jersey shore, but this doesn't even compare. with all this syria war talk going on, i was worried it could be a missile, or something of that nature since it left a fiery trail as it first entered and moved left across the sky. maybe it was a comet? but the fact that it hovered, was glowing orange, and made obvious conscious movements in the sky, it had to be controlled by something, and was definately not a natural occurrence.

content.detailedDescription:
At approximately 10 pm on september 4th 2013 i walked outside to smoke a cigarette. i walked out to the driveway and looked at the sky. there was a bright white object, by far the brightest in the sky, at appr. two oclock if 12 is directly above my head. it outshown everything in the sky by far and appeared to be about the size of a dime. i have no idea how big that makes it since it was in the sky, ya know? with a speed that is hard to describe it moved across the sky beyond my horizon view. very very fast. it made no sound. it left no trail and the light did not waiver in any way at all. i have seen shooting stars before. this was.Not. a shooting star. 
i didn't have time to think when i saw it, the entire episode, while it was in view, was too fast. but i know what i saw!
as soon as it was gone i walked down the street in the direction it went, searching the sky. my skin was covered in goosebumps, the hairs on my body standing up. i was completely filled with curiosity and fear. i have never experienced emotions like these together.
i stayed outside for approximately 30 minutes.
as soon as the object left the sky three manmade objects began patrolling the area. the were not large, had one white light and one red. one of the two was blinking, i think the white but honestly don't recall for certain. i assumed they were drones, for they were not very large either. they patrolled the area of the sky where i viewed the object and were still patrolling when i went inside.
about an hour or less later i came back out. the three objects were still patrolling. at this time i witnessed a meteor burn up in the atmosphere. it was short lived and no where near as bright as what i saw earlier.
the next day i saw that nasa has captured the meteor on film. though i did see the meteor, it is not  what i saw first and am reporting. also, why did nasa have our sky monitored to catch this meteor, if not because it was searching for the object i saw.
i have gone outside on the nights since looking for the manmade objects, and of course the ufo, and have not seen any of them since.
content.summary: Looked up, bright unwavering light moved at incredible speed from 2 oclock to horizon. followed by 3 manmade vehicles patrolling.

content.detailedDescription:
Friday september 6 2013 at approximately 8:30 pm my husband and i were driving to the bookstore. we were in our car travelling north on king street in waterloo when my husband noticed a unusual number of orange yellow lights in the night sky above and in front of us and brought my attention to them. we thought initially these must be aeroplanes and how strange it was to see that many planes so close together. they appeared to be star-orb shaped but much bigger than stars flying west to east. the yellowy orange lights remained solid, they didn't flash. they appeared to be flying in twos at the same altitude  but in no specific formation, sort of staggered and irregularly spaced.  i observed one of the first three lights move quickly and close to  another light ahead of it. we initially counted six lights but soon spotted another four following. we kept driving on our same course and lost sighting in the cloud cover. we felt puzzled as to what we had just witnessed. it was unlike anything either of us had ever seen before.

  approximately 45 min after the sighting we saw an aeroplane in the sky as we exited the book store. it had the typical 3 lights, blue red and white and middle one was flashing. it was definitely not the same type of object in comparison to what we had seen earlier.
content.summary: Nine or more orange lights moving seemingly in pairs west to east
